<ul class = 'definition' data-word = 'Vector'>
  <li>
    A <strong>vector</strong> is a quantity
    that includes both magnitude and direction.
  </li>
  <li>
    In the equation above,
    initial velocity,
    final velocity, and acceleration are vectors.
  </li>
  <li>
    In one-dimensional problems (in this pod),
    the direction is represented by a positive
    or negative sign,
    and the magnitude is represented by the absolute
    value of a quantity.
  </li>
</ul>
<p class = 'definition' data-word = 'Speed'>
  The magnitude of the velocity vector
  is called the <strong>speed</strong>.
  It can be found by taking the absolute
  value of the velocity.
</p>



